uch fundamental issues as inheritance or choice of marriage partner.Negotiation and Resistance upends the received view of this period in French history as one in which lords dealt harshly and without opposition toward subservient peasants, offering numerous examples of peasants standing up against those who would dominate them.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 05. Dez 2022) 0aAutonomy (Psychology)zFrancexHistoryyTo 1500. 0aCivilization, Medieval. 0aPeasantszFrance, NorthernxEconomic conditionsyTo 1500. 0aPeasantszFrance, NorthernxSocial conditionsyTo 1500. 4aLEGAL HISTORY & STUDIES. 4aWest European History. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  amedieval peasants in Burgundy-Champagne, medieval cartularies, peasant opportunity and agency in Medieval France, medieval economic and agricultural history, Feudal revolution and mutations, crisis of the 12th century.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311075182640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150176725840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501767258423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501767258/original  a978-3-11-075182-6  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK